eace and a custodian of the virtues and norms of a civilized and functional international society—in sum a "courtier of civilization."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDiplomacy. 0aInternational relations. 4aHistory : History. 4aPolitics and Law : International Relations. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438448947423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438448947/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles